ms are the same."]}]},{"name":"Raymond","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Raimund</i>, of Germanic origin, from <i>ragin</i> ‘advice, decision’ + <i>mund</i> ‘protector’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. Subsequently it dropped out of use, but was revived in the middle of the 19th century, together with several other given names of Old English and Norman origin."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Raymond De Lunel V was born in 1195, in France, his father, Raimond Gaucelm IV de LUNEL, was 12 and his mother, Guise, was 10. He had at least 1 daughter with Ermengarde Adhémar de Monteil. He died in 1262, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1195–1262":"1195–1262","1200–Female":"1200–Surnud","1235–1296":"1235–1296","1184–1215":"1184–1215","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1200":"1200","5 April 1215":"5. aprill 1215","1296":"1296","1262":"1262","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1184":"1184","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1195–1262":"1195–1262","1200–Female":"1200–Kuollut","1235–1296":"1235–1296","1184–1215":"1184–1215","1185–Female":"1185–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1200":"1200","5 April 1215":"5. huhtikuuta 1215","1296":"1296","1262":"1262","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1184":"1184","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1195–1262":"1195–1262","1200–Female":"1200–Décédée","1235–1296":"1235–1296","1184–1215":"1184–1215","1185–Female":"1185–Décédée","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1200":"1200","5 April 1215":"5 avril 1215","1296":"1296","1262":"1262","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1184":"1184","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Raymond De Lunel V est né en 1195, à France, son père, Raimond Gaucelm IV de LUNEL, avait 12 ans et sa mère, Guise, avait 10 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Ermengarde Adhémar de Monteil. Il est décédé en 1262, à l’âge de 67 ans."},"de":{"1195–1262":"1195–1262","1200–Female":"1200–Verstorben"